\begin{table}
\captionsetup{labelformat=empty}
\caption{Table 1
Classification and frequency of the six error types}
\begin{tabular}{|l|l|l|l|l|}
\hline Error types & Definition & Measurement & Tolerance & Frequency of occurrence (\%) \\
\hline Tiny faces & The overall extent of each face is too small & The diagonal length of the bounding box of a face & Extent \( <0.05 \mathrm{~mm} \) & 29 \\
\hline Narrow regions & A narrow portion of a face & The maximum width of the narrow portion of a face & Max. width \( <0.02 \mathrm{~mm} \) & 11 \\
\hline Non-tangent faces & A non-tangent angle between adjacent faces(a \( \mathrm{G}^{1} \) discontinuity) & The maximum angle between surface normals evaluated at pairs of the nearest points on each face along a common edge ( \( \mathrm{C}^{0} \) discontinuity) & Angle \( >1.0^{\circ} \) & 5 \\
\hline Narrow steps & A narrow portion of a face that forms a sharp step between adjacent faces & The maximum width of the narrow portion of a face & Max. width \( <0.02 \mathrm{~mm} \) & 17 \\
\hline Sharp face angles & A large angle between adjacent faces & The maximum angle between pairs of face normal vectors along a common boundary & Angle \( <1.0^{\circ} \) & 3 \\
\hline Narrow spaces & A narrow portion of the space surrounding a solid & The maximum width of the narrow space & Max. width \( <0.01 \mathrm{~mm} \) & 16 \\
\hline
\end{tabular}
\end{table}
